          "claim3_text": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The idea of a revolution might be a frightening thought to anyone who has benefited from the racial caste system in America, but simply told, this country was born from revolution. Revolution against British policing of the American colonies led to modern-day America. Revolution against French colonialism in Haiti led to the first Black-led republic. Revolution in South Africa led to the end of apartheid. While we may look unfavorably at the practices of revolution when we apply the lens of race in this country, it has long been a vehicle for much of the progress we have made as a society, which everyone benefits from. Black people are 13% of our country’s population but have consistently forced America to actualize its founding promises. As long as the conditions that caused the American Revolution are still in existence, the need for revolution remains just as strong today."
            }
          ],
